The paper deals with computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation, and proposes a novel architecture for improving the performance of convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture, which involves optimization and modeling, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also involves neural networks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
